<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,890,1196]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,996,1021]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small tree-trunk dwelling jumping spiders. Resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zabka, 1996" authorityName="Zabka" authorityYear="1996" box="[950,1183,992,1020]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bulolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[950,1032,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Bulolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zabka, M." box="[1040,1183,992,1020]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="701 - 707" refId="ref31296" refString="Zabka, M. (1996) Bulolia, a new genus of Salticidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Papua New Guinea. Revue suisse de Zoologie, vol. hors serie 2, 701 - 707." type="journal article" year="1996">Żabka, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Balogh, 1980 a" authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1980" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Leptathamas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1341,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Leptathamas</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Balogh, P." pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="29 - 31" refId="ref30026" refString="Balogh, P. (1980 a) Studies on the Papuan Attidae (Araneae): Leptathamas paradoxus gen. et sp. n. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 41, 29 - 31." type="journal article" year="1980">Balogh, 1980a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(also see Szű 
<bibRefCitation author="Szuts, T." box="[381,467,1031,1055]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="41 - 57" refId="ref31077" refString="Szuts, T. (2003) On remarkable jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) from Papua New Guinea. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 64, 41 - 57." type="journal article" year="2003">ts 2003</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Thorell" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1881" box="[535,789,1031,1055]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Coccorchestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[535,697,1031,1055]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Coccorchestes</emphasis>
Thorell
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Balogh, P." box="[854,1016,1031,1055]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="61 - 88" refId="ref30062" refString="Balogh, P. (1980 b) The genus Coccorchestes Thorell, 1881 (Araneae: Attidae). Acta Zoologica Hungarica, 26, 61 - 88." type="journal article" year="1980">Balogh 1980b</bibRefCitation>
) in the sperm duct of the male palp forming a loop at the prolateral side of the bulb, but can be easily distinguished by the body form and color pattern (
<figureCitation box="[159,326,1102,1126]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 272–275" captionStart-1="FIGURES 276–281" captionStartId-0="58.[151,263,1468,1491]" captionStartId-1="59.[151,263,1666,1689]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,193,1447]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1431,227,1639]" captionTargetId-0="figure-193@58.[151,1436,193,1447]" captionTargetId-1="figure-108@59.[151,1436,227,1645]" captionTargetPageId-0="58" captionTargetPageId-1="59" captionText-0="FIGURES 272–275. Variratina minuta sp. nov. 272–273 male holotype; 274–275 female paratype. FIGURES 272–275 are copyright © 2012 W. P. Maddison, released under a Creative Commons Attribution (CC–BY) 3.0 license." captionText-1="FIGURES 276–281. Variratina minuta sp. nov. 276 male holotype, dorsal view; 277 female paratype, dorsal view; 278 male left palp, ventral view; 279 male left palp, retrolateral view; 280 epigynum, ventral view; 281 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 276, 0.5 mm; 277, 0.2 mm; 278–281, 0.1 mm." pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 272–277</figureCitation>
). ALEs and AMEs are in typical salticid configuration (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1187,1102,1126]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 272–275" captionStart-1="FIGURES 276–281" captionStartId-0="58.[151,263,1468,1491]" captionStartId-1="59.[151,263,1666,1689]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,193,1447]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1431,227,1639]" captionTargetId-0="figure-193@58.[151,1436,193,1447]" captionTargetId-1="figure-108@59.[151,1436,227,1645]" captionTargetPageId-0="58" captionTargetPageId-1="59" captionText-0="FIGURES 272–275. Variratina minuta sp. nov. 272–273 male holotype; 274–275 female paratype. FIGURES 272–275 are copyright © 2012 W. P. Maddison, released under a Creative Commons Attribution (CC–BY) 3.0 license." captionText-1="FIGURES 276–281. Variratina minuta sp. nov. 276 male holotype, dorsal view; 277 female paratype, dorsal view; 278 male left palp, ventral view; 279 male left palp, retrolateral view; 280 epigynum, ventral view; 281 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 276, 0.5 mm; 277, 0.2 mm; 278–281, 0.1 mm." pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 272–277</figureCitation>
), unlike 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zabka" authorityYear="1996" box="[1298,1380,1102,1126]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bulolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1298,1380,1102,1126]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Bulolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Balogh" authorityYear="1980" box="[151,296,1137,1161]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Leptathamas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,296,1137,1161]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Leptathamas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whose ALEs are posterior to the AMEs. Also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1881" box="[1002,1164,1137,1161]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Coccorchestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1164,1137,1161]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Coccorchestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its carapace lacking crenellated posterior margin overlying the abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[746,905,1172,1196]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 272–275" captionStart-1="FIGURES 276–281" captionStartId-0="58.[151,263,1468,1491]" captionStartId-1="59.[151,263,1666,1689]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,193,1447]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1431,227,1639]" captionTargetId-0="figure-193@58.[151,1436,193,1447]" captionTargetId-1="figure-108@59.[151,1436,227,1645]" captionTargetPageId-0="58" captionTargetPageId-1="59" captionText-0="FIGURES 272–275. Variratina minuta sp. nov. 272–273 male holotype; 274–275 female paratype. FIGURES 272–275 are copyright © 2012 W. P. Maddison, released under a Creative Commons Attribution (CC–BY) 3.0 license." captionText-1="FIGURES 276–281. Variratina minuta sp. nov. 276 male holotype, dorsal view; 277 female paratype, dorsal view; 278 male left palp, ventral view; 279 male left palp, retrolateral view; 280 epigynum, ventral view; 281 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 276, 0.5 mm; 277, 0.2 mm; 278–281, 0.1 mm." pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 272–277</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
